definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + maltose -eq- CoA + acetyl-maltose.

Catalysis of the specific cleavage of the beta-(1--gt-4) glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramyl and N-acetylglucosaminyl residues in peptidoglycan, with the concomitant formation of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetylmuramyl residues. Acts on linkages within peptidoglycan chains (i.e. not at the ends) to produce shorter strands with 1,6-anhydromuramic acid ends.

Catalysis of the specific cleavage of the beta-(1--gt-4) glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramyl and N-acetylglucosaminyl residues in peptidoglycan, with the concomitant formation of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetylmuramyl residues.

Catalysis of the integration of prophage DNA into a target DNA molecule, usually a bacterial chromosome, via a sequence-specific recombination event which involves the formation of an intasome, a DNA-protein-complex designed for site-specific recombination of the phage and host DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + propanoate -eq- ADP + propanoyl phosphate.

Catalysis of the PEP-dependent, phosphoryl transfer-driven transport of substances across a membrane. The transport happens by catalysis of the reaction -  protein N-phosphohistidine + sugar(out) -eq- protein histidine + sugar phosphate(in). This differs from primary and secondary active transport in that the solute is modified during transport.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein L-glutamate -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein L-glutamate 5-methyl ester -  this reaction is the methylation of peptidyl-L-glutamate to form peptidyl-L-glutamate 5-methyl ester.
